00:00:26.565 --> 00:00:28.590
So we wanted to create
a space where students

00:00:28.590 --> 00:00:31.080
can come and be comfortable --
all students, not just

00:00:31.080 --> 00:00:32.759
students with disabilities.

00:00:32.759 --> 00:00:35.100
We intentionally
designed the space

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:37.440
for physical and
technical access,

00:00:37.440 --> 00:00:39.570
but we want it to be
also a place where

00:00:39.570 --> 00:00:42.690
we can foster conversation,
to educate our community,

00:00:42.690 --> 00:00:45.150
where we can help
students with disabilities

00:00:45.150 --> 00:00:48.144
to have a voice on campus, and
to provide some programming.

00:00:48.144 --> 00:00:49.560
MONICA MAGALHAES:
The thing that's

00:00:49.560 --> 00:00:51.684
different about this space
is that the space really

00:00:51.684 --> 00:00:53.580
